data.content:
Three breaking changes affect your code. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`

Your manual expression tree building **won't compile** anymore. The good news: it's now drastically simpler.

```csharp
// EF Core 10 ŌĆö no more expression trees needed
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö two changes

**a) Shared names are now uniquified.** If `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously mapped to the same `Street` column (data corruption risk), EF 10 appends a number (e.g. `Street`, `Street1`). To preserve the old shared column name explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` used to produce column `BillingAddress_City`; now it produces `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To keep the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ Both changes affect **migrations** ŌĆö a new migration will generate column renames. Pin names with `HasColumnName` if you have existing data.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gains a `string logCommandText` parameter (contains redacted SQL for logging):

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the actual executed SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
